<br>
<br>
Since pulls were often double or even triple, with no mezzer, I could use RAINS on mobs hitting them with all waves.<br>
Now rains on 2 mobs is UBER sweet efficiency. Rains have sucky resists but when on 2 mobs and with reasonable resist rates you generally get 3 waves hitting. With mage earring reducing mana, and possible crits, rooting or heavy aggroing mobs/slowing/stunning, perhaps RAINING is actually more efficient than mezzing? Both mobs die VERy fast.<br>
<br>
Wizzies, far as I know, suffer less resists, I'd assume on rains to? Has anyone tried getting say 2+ wizzies in a group, on double pulls root/aggro mobs then DOT mez etc but let wizzies rain? If a typical xp mob has 5-6k hp at high end, each rain could do over 1khp per wiz? Rains also cause less aggro.<br>
<br>
Just an idea <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Redorious<br>
Archmage<br>
karana<br>
