<br>
Rains, however, will work.  The resists are kinda ugly, but not as bad as people tend to think (except that whole last hit won't kill crap)<br>
<br>
Get two wizards, a slower and three melees into most zones and you can pull this off extremely well with proper aggro management.<br>
<br>
--Shardanaan<br>
Sorcerer, Torv <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utelegareth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telegareth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 5:16:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17769.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double pulls &amp; Rains = efficiency?</span><hr size=1> 2 - Warrior<br>
