The Nameless</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufirkang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>firkang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 5:25:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17769.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double pulls &amp; Rains = efficiency?</span><hr size=1> rains are equally resisted on wizards, but i do not have tears of prexus.  Anyone have this spell?  Is it a cold based rain? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umarttog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marttog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 5:54:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17769.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double pulls &amp; Rains = efficiency?</span><hr size=1> If I'm ever in a group with another wizard, it is more efficient to pull 8 mobs and AE them.<br>
