<br>
Firkang:  Tears of Prexus is cold based and can be found where the rest of the high level wiz spells are.  i.e. SF, Juggs.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 8:45:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17769.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double pulls &amp; Rains = efficiency?</span><hr size=1> Two questions.<br>
<br>
Last I recall, only 4 waves max of a rain can hit, so if two targets, then max two waves each.  Having abandoned <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sirocco</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in favor of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shock of Fiery Blades</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a while ago, I would be unaware of this being fixed.<br>
<br>
Second, do waves really have a greater chance of being resisted, or is it an illusion?  That is, supposed a check versus fire against a given opponent has an 80% of hitting for full, and ignoring partial resists, a rain with three waves would have about a 50/50 chance of getting at least one wave resisted, which would lead to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;myth&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that resists on rains suck.<br>
<br>
Or is it real?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Master ArchMage Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufirkang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>firkang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 8:58:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17769.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double pulls &amp; Rains = efficiency?</span><hr size=1> I have 59 wiz, 60 mage.  Hunting in akheva.....<br>
<br>
If i cast shock of fiery blades, NEVER a resist.  <br>
Sirroco many resists, some partial which is your myth theory but still all 3 waves are sometimes resisted and never on shock.  <br>
<br>
Same with wizard.  Any draught spell never a resist, rains, always a resist of 1-3 waves.<br>
<br>
But still casting rains is better, 6 waves using 2 chars and a pet the mob is almost dead even if some of them are resisted.<br>
I am sure malosini would help things, but there is no need with the low hp of akheva mobs.<br>
<br>
For 2 mobs i still root one away so i can get 6 waves on the target.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Condescension, by CK<BR><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=1111.topic>Freddy</a>, incognito.</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 9:24:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17769.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double pulls &amp; Rains = efficiency?</span><hr size=1> Wizzies suffer no less resists than anyone else.<br>
<br>
Rains just suck. It's the dream of the potential of rains that makes so many people (including me) waste so much time on them. But the resists just make it net out to mush less dmg/mana than regular dd.<br>
<br>
But I'm over it. They are inneficient in actual use and unreliable and unwieldly.<br>
<br>
Hell Al'Kabor spells actually have a use for farming. These are just a waste of spellslots.<br>
<br>
They should resist like normal nukes. Then they still wouldn't be that great but in certain situations could be useful.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urhiandedanaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhian Dedanaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 10:28:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17769.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double pulls &amp; Rains = efficiency?</span><hr size=1> I disagree about the general run of rains.  I find them very useful and efficient, but very situational.<br>
<br>
I run a nice little log parser that works realtime, so I can have numerical data as well as my emotional 'feel' about what is working.  In Halls of Testing last week, I was getting two fulls and one partial on most rains (Tears of Solusek) on the cold-basted wurms.  645+645+~250 = approx 1540 damage for 415mana = 3.7 damage per mana point on average, with lower aggro than nukes.  I was having no difficulty averaging 7K damage on most of the wurms, not bad for 1/30th the raid force.  /grin  Even kept a mana reserve for point-blank fast nukes for gaters.<br>
<br>
A mage buddy and I love using rains for XP hunting, too.  I'll click the Jboots and run out and grab just about anything Skyfire has to offer (/hugs SoTF), bring it back and he'll sicc his pet on it.  Ten seconds for pet aggro and we each drop one rain, then I BoF the runner as we both sit to medd and the pet finishes it off.  Total mana expenditure per pull is 1 Rain and 1 BoF, he casts 1 Rain and heals pet once.  Aggro is low enough that a taunting pet is enough to keep it busy.  With medding as the pet finishes it, I seldom have to stop if we have so much as Clarity 1.  <br>
<br>
There are plenty of reasons not to use rains - mezzes for cc, mobs that ping-pong, tanks that move too much.  But give me a speedbump and I'll usually have a rain memmed.<br>
<br>
Rhian,<br>
56 wizard,<br>
Xegony <p>Rhian DeDanaan, 56 Wizard, Xegony<BR><BR>

