Incidentally the alleged resist reduction was only to normal blasts as far as I've heard, it did nothing to AE spells (you would be better off as a Magician if you used Malise spells on the monsters). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 6/20/02 4:35:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 4:45:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17769.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-side-01.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double pulls &amp; Rains = efficiency?</span><hr size=1> It should be noted that there are a number of people out there who quietly fail to encounter the enormous amount of resists everyone says they find with rains.<br>
<br>
